meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Salis","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Ruben, Amparo, Armando, Emilio, Juana, Rodolfo.","Italian (Sardinia): plural form of   Sale   ‘salt’.","French: variant of <b>Salies</b>, a habitational name from a placename Salies in Haute-Garonne and Pyrénées-Atlantiques, ultimately derived from Latin <i>salina</i> ‘salt marsh, salt pan, saltworks’."],"variants":[{"name":"Sale","meanings":["English: habitational name from Sale (Cheshire), or from any of several minor places or topographic features named from Middle English <i>sale</i>, <i>salle</i> ‘sallow, willow’ (Old English <i>s(e)alh</i>). See also   Seal  , with which this name may often have interchanged.","English: from Middle English <i>sal(e)</i> ‘hall’ (Old English <i>sæl</i>, Old French <i>sale</i>, Old Norse <i>salr</i>), translated by medieval clerks as Latin <i>aula</i>. The surname may be topographic, for someone who lived or worked in a hall, or occupational, for someone who worked at a hall as a servant. This was the name of an Anglo-Norman family who had settled in County Tipperary, Ireland, by the 13th century. The name was Gaelicized as <b>de Sál</b>, hence the Anglicized form   Saul   which has been widely adopted in Ireland.","Croatian (<b>Šale</b>): probably from a pet form of the personal name <i>Šanto</i>, a Croatized form of Italian   Santo  ."]}]},{"name":"Béliarde","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Altered (shortened) form of French   Bellegarde  . This surname is most common among Native Americans in ND, namely the Turtle Mountain Band of Chippewa Indians and the Spirit Lake Tribe of Dakota Sioux. It is also found in Haiti."],"variants":[{"name":"Bellegarde","meanings":["French (mainly southwestern): habitational name from (La) Bellegarde or (La) Belle Garde, names of several places in various parts of France, e.g. Bellegarde-du-Gard, named with Old French <i>garde</i> ‘watch, protection’ (see   Garde  ) and designating a stronghold. This surname is also found in Haiti. Compare   Belgard   and   Belgarde  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Béliarde de Salis was born about 1070, in Salies-du-Salat, Haute-Garonne, Occitanie, France. She had at least 1 son with Lord Bertrand de Comps."},"et":{"environ 1070–":"umbes 1070–Surnud","1060–Male":"1060–Surnud","1095–1163":"1095–1163","1070–Female":"1070–Surnud","about 1095":"umbes 1095","1163":"1163","environ 1070":"umbes 1070","1095":"1095","1060":"1060","1070":"1070","Comps-sur-Artuby, Var, Provence-Alpes-Côte d'Azur, FRANCE,":"Comps-sur-Artuby, Var, Prantsusmaa","Salies-du-Salat, Haute-Garonne, Occitanie, France":"Salies-du-Salat, Haute-Garonne, Occitanie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"environ 1070–":"noin 1070–Kuollut","1060–Male":"1060–Kuollut","1095–1163":"1095–1163","1070–Female":"1070–Kuollut","about 1095":"noin 1095","1163":"1163","environ 1070":"noin 1070","1095":"1095","1060":"1060","1070":"1070","Comps-sur-Artuby, Var, Provence-Alpes-Côte d'Azur, FRANCE,":"Comps-sur-Artuby, Var, Ranska","Salies-du-Salat, Haute-Garonne, Occitanie, France":"Salies-du-Salat, Haute-Garonne, Occitanie, Ranska"},"fr":{"environ 1070–":"environ 1070–Décédée","1060–Male":"1060–Décédé","1095–1163":"1095–1163","1070–Female":"1070–Décédée","about 1095":"environ 1095","1163":"1163","environ 1070":"environ 1070","1095":"1095","1060":"1060","1070":"1070","Comps-sur-Artuby, Var, Provence-Alpes-Côte d'Azur, FRANCE,":"Comps-sur-Artuby, Var, France","Salies-du-Salat, Haute-Garonne, Occitanie, 